    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 358
                    The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations (
                        Pauley
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State
                    
                    Sent to the Acting Secretary of State over the
                        signature of Harriman.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d358</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">358</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-06-25T12:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-06-25T12:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-25T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="358" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/6–2545: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 358<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PEW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pauley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d358fn1">Sent to the Acting Secretary of State over the
                        signature of <persName corresp="#p_HK1">Harriman</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-25T20:00:00+03:00">June 25, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2262. <gloss target="#t_topsec1">TopSec</gloss> from <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName> for Secretary.</p>
                <p>Supplementing my wire of June 19<note n="2" xml:id="d358fn2">
                        <ref target="#d356">Document No. 356</ref>.</note> relating to allocation
                    formula foi reparations between the Big Three, after conferring with <gloss target="#t_reps1">rep</gloss> of the <pb facs="0645" n="513" xml:id="pg_513"/>
                    <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>,<note n="3" xml:id="d358fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MSW1">Sir Walter Monckton</persName>.</note> I would
                    now propose that in addition to public statement that Big Three will give up
                    proportionately to other nations as may appear justified, it shall also be
                    understood between the Big Three that unless all of the Big Three ultimately
                    agree on the actual amounts to be allowed other nations and do in fact make such
                    amounts available on the basis of 55, 22½, and 22½ percent respectively, then
                    the whole question of distribution of reparations between the Big Three
                    themselves shall be reopened.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
